Package project1

Class FitnessClass

java.lang.Object
project1.FitnessClass
public class FitnessClass extends Object
MemberDatabast class to store members inside a member list. Performs add and remove member, display members with or without order.
Author:
Songyuan Zhang, Robert Jimenez

  • Constructor Details

    • FitnessClass

      public FitnessClass(String className, Time startTime, String instructor)
      Initialize a FitnessClass object. Initialize one FitnessClass object with class name, start time, and instructor.
      Parameters:
      className - the name of the fitness class
      startTime - the start time of the fitness class, it can be either morning or afternoon
      instructor - the name of the instructor of the fitness class

  • Method Details

    • find

      private int find(Member member)
      Check whether the member is in the student list. Traverse the student list to find the student.
      Parameters:
      member - the member that needs to be found.
      Returns:
      index if the member is found, Compare.NOT_FOUND otherwise.

    • grow

      private void grow()
      Increase the capacity of the student list if it has reached its capacity. Copying old array elements into the array with the new capacity.

    • checkInClass

      public boolean checkInClass(Member member)
      Allow member to check into a class if the student has not checked in. Find whether the student is in the class student list. Add the student into the list by appending to the end of the list.
      Parameters:
      member - the member that needs to be checked in.
      Returns:
      true if the member is check in successfully, false if the member is already checked in.

    • checkExistence

      public boolean checkExistence(Member member)
      Check whether student has already checked into this class. Called by GymManager class to check time conflict in the class schedule.
      Parameters:
      member - the member who wants to check in another class that might have time conflict with this class.
      Returns:
      true if the member has already checked in, false if the member has not checked in.

    • checkEmptyStudentList

      public boolean checkEmptyStudentList()
      Check whether the student list is empty. Called by GymManager class to help listFitnessClassSchedule method to see whether the class has student or not.
      Returns:
      true if the class has no student, false if otherwise.

    • dropClass

      public boolean dropClass(Member member)
      Drop a class for a member. If member exists in the class, drop the member from the student list. Move every subsequence members on position to the left of the array.
      Parameters:
      member - who wants to drop the class.
      Returns:
      true if the class has been dropped, false if student is not in the class.

    • getStudentList

      public Member[] getStudentList()
      Get the list of students checked into the class. Called by GymManager class to print list of students in a class.
      Returns:
      studentList containing list of students checked into the class.

    • toString

      public String toString()
      Override the toString method and print class name, instructor, and start time of the class.
      Overrides:
      toString in class Object
      Returns:
      string containing class name, instructor, and start time of the class.
